<taxonomicName id="59A8F450EC5CC9A8489704E2CB0F755B" class="Liliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Micrastelia" species="waialealae" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Micrastelia</taxonomicName>
Skottsb., Kongl. Svenska Vetenskapsakad. Handl. ser. 3, 14(2): 56. 1934.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AF265D4D5B02A8F07604EC064A816142" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" type="note">
<paragraph id="E4FE8C8C60E775D5DD21FCF719DBE703" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4222623FF4B3DDD69ED5634577220C36" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">
Low, compact, turf forming growth form; leaves caniculate; inflorescence bearing few flowers; staminate flowers with short filaments (0.6-1.9 mm); pistillate flowers with short outer tepals (2.6-3.8 
<normalizedToken id="A187A53DBE675462550BE66F71B6A8C4" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.8-1.3 mm); ovary trilocular, intermediate length (2.6-3.8 mm); fruit ellipsoid, many seeds per fruit (17-24); seeds short and narrow (1.1-1.7 
<normalizedToken id="B7E239DB3966A042188ADFBA44C4D3EF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-0.8 mm). Type: 
<taxonomicName id="FFF5F42B02CEFFF84B8FC55CBDCFA487" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia pumila" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pumila">
<emphasis id="02C5561E729AAAE6C6C85559611DAE4D" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Astelia pumila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Forst.) Gaudich.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DD5DB4EDA2A880258CC82AC21B795744" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="59B258CC18D5947DE8A2191957B29090" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="504920D29DC8B9830B54C5C3D81C7E66" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">
The relationships of 
<taxonomicName id="6887378DA7D2A44328FECEBF04EA33E5" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Micrastelia" species="pumila" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Micrastelia</taxonomicName>
are poorly resolved, with alternate relationships with 
<taxonomicName id="6B827CC810E0E359707D543A4D8EB5A7" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Asteliopsis) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="pumila" subGenus="Asteliopsis" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Asteliopsis</taxonomicName>
and the clade containing 
<taxonomicName id="54E83D98DCCB9C9BCD45BBAB34B0FF75" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Tricella) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="pumila" subGenus="Tricella" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Tricella</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="10F86523B96FA4DE5290E2168383CA1A" authority="Skottsberg, 1934" authorityName="Birch" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Collospermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Collospermum" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D2706BF433CC50AFB75684164283D694" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Collospermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Birch unpublished PhD thesis 2011, 
<bibRefCitation id="21CD144DA04E7943AAF5B072E428563D" author="Birch, JL" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="12" pageNumber="117" pagination="102 - 115" publicationUrl="10.1016/j.ympev.2012.05.031" refId="B2" refString="Birch, JL, Keeley, SC, Morden, CW, 2012. Molecular phylogeny and dating of Asteliaceae (Asparagales): Astelia s.l. evolution provides insight into the Oligocene history of New Zealand. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 65: 102 - 115, DOI: 10.1016/j.ympev.2012.05.031" title="Molecular phylogeny and dating of Asteliaceae (Asparagales): Astelia s. l. evolution provides insight into the Oligocene history of New Zealand." url="10.1016/j.ympev.2012.05.031" volume="65" year="2012">Birch et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="CA184D9F8C635BA1F70A8C1D21EEF5D6" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Microastelia" species="pumila" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Microastelia</taxonomicName>
contains a single species, 
<taxonomicName id="2944F215C5F1B60C26B752611262AD3F" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia pumila" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pumila">
<emphasis id="6454BF73CDD87237E06CFFEC2935C68D" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Astelia pumila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is a compact, turf-forming plant and dominant component of 
<taxonomicName id="D6321C996636A00728C9091BFDD0E01F" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1744E5AADBBAD4529F8B8425DB971E88" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Astelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
moorland in Chile, the Falkland Islands, and Tierra del Fuego. As a cushion-forming species, it differs morphologically from 
<taxonomicName id="89AAE81060BBAF48DD54D67B95830E6D" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Asteliopsis) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="pumila" subGenus="Asteliopsis" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Asteliopsis</taxonomicName>
, which contains species with open, spreading growth form that are epiphytic or terrestrial and primarily found of the understory in lowland to montane forests. 
<taxonomicName id="6E3961C8FC825325C829570F085770D5" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia pumila" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pumila">
<emphasis id="FC38F7D2C996777BED990826B665E635" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Astelia pumila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does share morphological features with 
<taxonomicName id="E05A0FB58810F2D13475A1E8CF417EAB" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Asteliopsis) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="pumila" subGenus="Asteliopsis" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Asteliopsis</taxonomicName>
(e.g. short pistillode or pistil) and, alternatively, with 
<taxonomicName id="92E28B4AC6DD975F0999AB805041B53A" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Collospermum) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="pumila" subGenus="Collospermum" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Collospermum</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F622A46AEA8B56418C689304EBB41F71" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Tricella) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="pumila" subGenus="Tricella" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Tricella</taxonomicName>
(e.g. seeds with a short, truncate funicle). The subgeneric placement of 
<taxonomicName id="16DD1A3FACC582BD6602FA82E37209C3" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Micrastelia" species="pumila" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Micrastelia</taxonomicName>
remains equivocal and the section is unplaced (
<emphasis id="323A255100944E54FC5FA2B2AF3B5B3F" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">incertae sedis</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F72AADBCF906FEA4F8075EE718585D88" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" type="included species and distribution">
<paragraph id="10A55A27B28BD37F99B341032524AD2C" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Included species and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A290C2FFFFEBC77CBD0C11618573A65D" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">
Chile, Falkland Islands, Tierra del Fuego: 
<taxonomicName id="FA1C7BD15A98CB61D1920CCB2118379B" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia pumila" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pumila">
<emphasis id="9CB6388C3FA559E29658F29E7C1BDE4B" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Astelia pumila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Forst.) Gaudich.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0A130F4D2083DBB7F0C29C4904CA6E5D" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="89EAB2FB535B84A69587DCE1DEC8CC52" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A77BBFE9515B4DF6B221BC9A10A8280" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Lowland (low latitudes) to sub-alpine (mid and higher latitudes) herbfields particularly on wet substrates (seeps, swamps etc.).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
